12.0pt&#39;&gt;Represen=
tations in a request (e.g. PUT or POST) and representations in
a response (=
e.g. GET or a PUT) need not be absolutely the same. HTTP servers
are not da=
tabases that blindly store the data. Using PUT to update the mutable
parts =
of a resource is perfectly okay. At least, I don&#39;t see anything that
breaks=
 HTTP.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/blockquote&gt;

